definitions.definition: ( now rare without a qualifying word ) The red panda ( Ailurus fulgens ), a small raccoon -like animal of northeast Asia with reddish fur and a long, ringed tail . [from 19th c.]
( colloquial , also attributively ) Ellipsis of giant panda ( “ Ailuropoda melanoleuca ” ) . [from 19th c.]
( British , law enforcement , colloquial ) Ellipsis of panda car ( “ a black-and-white police car ” ) . [from 20th c.]

definitions.definition: A brahmin who acts as the hereditary superintendent of a particular ghat or temple , and is regarded as knowledgeable in matters of genealogy and ritual .
